{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"81f02cfc-00d6-4d78-b8d5-9425a44474f0","content":"You can install `dotnet-trace` as a standalone tool without the SDK by downloading it directly:\n\n```bash\n# Download the dotnet-trace global tool (no SDK needed)\ncurl -sSL https://aka.ms/dotnet-trace/linux-x64 -o dotnet-trace\nchmod +x dotnet-trace\n\n# Find your app's PID\n./dotnet-trace ps\n\n# Collect a CPU trace (uses the default \"cpu-sampling\" profile)\n./dotnet-trace collect -p <PID> --profile cpu-sampling\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- The `aka.ms/dotnet-trace/linux-x64` URL gives you a self-contained single-file binary — no SDK or runtime install required.\n- For **ARM64** containers, use `linux-arm64` instead.\n- The output `.nettrace` file can be copied out (`docker cp`) and opened in **Visual Studio**, **PerfView**, or converted to speedscope format with `--format speedscope`.\n- To limit collection duration, add `--duration 00:00:30` (30 seconds).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d45c3b64-6ca2-4909-af99-f851587b9761","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to get `dotnet-trace` into a Linux container that doesn't have the .NET SDK. This is a practical DevOps/.NET diagnostics question. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":323},"id":"fa2a7fd0-fb81-4d2a-bcbe-dc2f319bed1a","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:49:47.454Z","parentId":"1de4803c-7838-4109-8e85-7fca532916e8"}
